Text.SourceString: The ocean's depths hold endless inspiration.//Each wave, each grain of sand, each shimmering scale...they all tell a story.
Text.LocalizedString: The ocean's depths hold endless inspiration.//Each wave, each grain of sand, each shimmering scale...they all tell a story.

Text.SourceString: Tattooing is more than ink on skin...it's a sacred bond between artist and canvas.//<portrait=normal>Each tattoo I create is a part of someone's soul, etched in time.
Text.LocalizedString: Tattooing is more than ink on skin...it's a sacred bond between artist and canvas.//<portrait=normal>Each tattoo I create is a part of someone's soul, etched in time.

Text.SourceString: Here for a tattoo?
Text.LocalizedString: Here for a tattoo?

Text.SourceString: Oh, it's you. Come in if you must, but I'm rather busy.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it's you. Come in if you must, but I'm rather busy.

Text.SourceString: Oh, hey! It's you. Come in. How's the dry land treating ya?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, hey! It's you. Come in. How's the dry land treating ya?

Text.SourceString: The sea has its secrets. Not that they're anyone's business.
Text.LocalizedString: The sea has its secrets. Not that they're anyone's business.

Text.SourceString: The day's fine, I guess. If you're here to chat, I'm not in the mood.
Text.LocalizedString: The day's fine, I guess. If you're here to chat, I'm not in the mood.

Text.SourceString: The clients today have been a mixed bag. But that's the business.
Text.LocalizedString: The clients today have been a mixed bag. But that's the business.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the sea is calm today. Perfect for a moment of reflection and creativity.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the sea is calm today. Perfect for a moment of reflection and creativity.

Text.SourceString: Inspiration? It comes and goes. Not really something I discuss casually.
Text.LocalizedString: Inspiration? It comes and goes. Not really something I discuss casually.

Text.SourceString: I had some time to myself earlier. Just enough to clear my head.//Nothing more.
Text.LocalizedString: I had some time to myself earlier. Just enough to clear my head.//Nothing more.

Text.SourceString: I found this incredible shell near the palace today, and it sparked an idea for a tattoo.
Text.LocalizedString: I found this incredible shell near the palace today, and it sparked an idea for a tattoo.

Text.SourceString: Had some time to just float and think today. It's the simple pleasures, isn't it?
Text.LocalizedString: Had some time to just float and think today. It's the simple pleasures, isn't it?

Text.SourceString: It's cool chatting with you, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Feel free to drop by anytime.//My door's always open.
Text.LocalizedString: It's cool chatting with you, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Feel free to drop by anytime.//My door's always open.

Text.SourceString: There's something special about being outside, connecting with nature...makes me feel alive.
Text.LocalizedString: There's something special about being outside, connecting with nature...makes me feel alive.

Text.SourceString: I've seen the dry land...oh, yeah.//Even if I had feet, I don't think it's for me. It's much too bright up there.
Text.LocalizedString: I've seen the dry land...oh, yeah.//Even if I had feet, I don't think it's for me. It's much too bright up there.

Text.SourceString: Was it raining hard up there? The fact that we can feel the current shift...it usually is an indication.
Text.LocalizedString: Was it raining hard up there? The fact that we can feel the current shift...it usually is an indication.

Text.SourceString: I should go up there and check it out.
Text.LocalizedString: I should go up there and check it out.

Text.SourceString: The stars are usually brighter after a wave of rain. I'll have to check it out.
Text.LocalizedString: The stars are usually brighter after a wave of rain. I'll have to check it out.

Text.SourceString: For as long as I've lived here...I don't think I've ever seen a land-dweller being accepted like you.
Text.LocalizedString: For as long as I've lived here...I don't think I've ever seen a land-dweller being accepted like you.

Text.SourceString: The Kingdom jobs never interest me. I like to keep my creative freedom intact.
Text.LocalizedString: The Kingdom jobs never interest me. I like to keep my creative freedom intact.

Text.SourceString: The jobs there seem...restricting.
Text.LocalizedString: The jobs there seem...restricting.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Olan</> likes working for the royal family. He loves cooking more than anything.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Olan</> likes working for the royal family. He loves cooking more than anything.

Text.SourceString: He used to travel around the seas...pretty sure spent a lot of his adult life traveling.
Text.LocalizedString: He used to travel around the seas...pretty sure spent a lot of his adult life traveling.

Text.SourceString: A stormy sea churns up thoughts, just like it churns up the waves. It's a good day for creation.
Text.LocalizedString: A stormy sea churns up thoughts, just like it churns up the waves. It's a good day for creation.

Text.SourceString: Welcome to my creative haven. What can I design for you?
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome to my creative haven. What can I design for you?

Text.SourceString: I draw outside to breathe life into my art.
Text.LocalizedString: I draw outside to breathe life into my art.

Text.SourceString: The Summer sun ignites my passion for vivid colors and bold designs.//<portrait=happy>The water down here is warmer also...which I love.
Text.LocalizedString: The Summer sun ignites my passion for vivid colors and bold designs.//<portrait=happy>The water down here is warmer also...which I love.

Text.SourceString: The sea is my muse, always restless, always free.
Text.LocalizedString: The sea is my muse, always restless, always free.

Text.SourceString: I put my soul into every design. It's art that lives with you.
Text.LocalizedString: I put my soul into every design. It's art that lives with you.

Text.SourceString: Ink is permanent, but so are the stories it tells. Choose wisely.
Text.LocalizedString: Ink is permanent, but so are the stories it tells. Choose wisely.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes the quiet of my home is louder than any crowd. Do you feel it?
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes the quiet of my home is louder than any crowd. Do you feel it?

Text.SourceString: The current's strong today. Makes for a challenging swim, but I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: The current's strong today. Makes for a challenging swim, but I like it.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I spend my evening watching the fish. Their freedom is calming.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I spend my evening watching the fish. Their freedom is calming.

Text.SourceString: I've been trying this new seaweed blend for breakfast. It's surprisingly yummy.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been trying this new seaweed blend for breakfast. It's surprisingly yummy.

Text.SourceString: Some days, I just float on the waves and let them take me where they will. Wanna try it sometime?
Text.LocalizedString: Some days, I just float on the waves and let them take me where they will. Wanna try it sometime?

Text.SourceString: I've picked up a thing or two from <NPCName>Olan</> about eating well. He knows his way around flavors.
Text.LocalizedString: I've picked up a thing or two from <NPCName>Olan</> about eating well. He knows his way around flavors.

Text.SourceString: A good meal doesn't have to be fancy. Just real food, cooked simply. That's the secret.
Text.LocalizedString: A good meal doesn't have to be fancy. Just real food, cooked simply. That's the secret.

Text.SourceString: You know what's great? Finding a meal that's not just delicious but actually good for you. Simple pleasures.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what's great? Finding a meal that's not just delicious but actually good for you. Simple pleasures.

Text.SourceString: You ever taste <NPCName>Olan</>'s grilled sea kelp? There's something special about it. Healthy, too.
Text.LocalizedString: You ever taste <NPCName>Olan</>'s grilled sea kelp? There's something special about it. Healthy, too.

Text.SourceString: I rarely pay for anything in here. I usually get it from someone who doesn't want them anymore, or I make them myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I rarely pay for anything in here. I usually get it from someone who doesn't want them anymore, or I make them myself.

Text.SourceString: Those pots over there? Those are from <NPCName>Etna</>. She had extras.
Text.LocalizedString: Those pots over there? Those are from <NPCName>Etna</>. She had extras.

Text.SourceString: I don't like spending money on useless things. Tattoos, I understand; that's part of you, you know.//But golden-plated seats? Gemstones on cups? It's wasteful.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't like spending money on useless things. Tattoos, I understand; that's part of you, you know.//But golden-plated seats? Gemstones on cups? It's wasteful.

Text.SourceString: I get not liking land dwellers, but some merfolk here can be too intense about it...closed off, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: I get not liking land dwellers, but some merfolk here can be too intense about it...closed off, you know.

Text.SourceString: It's nice living here. There's always so much food around...you don't need to forage too far out.
Text.LocalizedString: It's nice living here. There's always so much food around...you don't need to forage too far out.

Text.SourceString: I don't go to the Deep Sea. Some parts of the sea don't want to be disturbed, and I oblige.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't go to the Deep Sea. Some parts of the sea don't want to be disturbed, and I oblige.

Text.SourceString: I don't feel very hungry, but I suppose I should eat soon...it's time.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't feel very hungry, but I suppose I should eat soon...it's time.

Text.SourceString: You're <PlayerName>$Player</>, huh? I'm <NPCName>Rysy</>.// caught wind of what you did for the coral tree. Pretty impressive stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: You're <PlayerName>$Player</>, huh? I'm <NPCName>Rysy</>.// caught wind of what you did for the coral tree. Pretty impressive stuff.

Text.SourceString: Hmm?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm?
